 | eBike T200 | 2 |\n| 12:46:59 | Pai-32 | Melissa Cameron | Afternoon | Process Variation | Repaired | eBike T101 | 3 |\n| 12:40:14 | Pai-32 | Deanna Miller | Weekend Night | Design Issue | Adjusted Process Parameters | eBike C150 | 2 |\n| 12:40:04 | Pai-31 | Jessica Green | Afternoon | Process Variation | Reworked | eBike T200 | 3 |\n| 14:01:30 | Pai-32 | Christopher Jimenez | Night | Process Variation | Repaired | eBike T101 | 3 |\n| 19:02:31 | Qua-71 | Sara Osborn | Morning | Material Defect | Adjusted Process Parameters | eBike T200 | 2 |\n\nGAPS / MISSING DATA\n\n• Cannot determine if Color Mismatch spike is anomalous or recurring pattern—only 7-day window provided; historical trend analysis requires longer baseline [source: data limitation]\n• No direct correlation data between specific maintenance activities and defect occurrence; causality cannot be established from timing alone [source: data limitation]\n• Operator skill/training levels not available; cannot assess whether Operator Error root cause reflects capability gaps or situational factors [source: data limitation]\n• Paint Booth material batch traceability not captured; Material Defect root cause cannot be linked to specific supplier lots or batch dates [source: data limitation]\n\nHANDOFF NOTES\n\n• Escalate Paint and Finish workcenters (Pai-31, Pai-32) for process parameter audit, especially around 13:00-14:00 window; focus on calibration drift post-maintenance (11:32-11:47 changeover) [source: fetch_defect_records, fetch_downtime_events]\n• Review Afternoon shift operator performance (Melissa Cameron, Kelsey Kaiser, Harold Foster) for training gaps; 6 of 13 defects occurred Afternoon shift with Operator Error cited 2x [source: fetch_operator_logs, fetch_defect_records]\n• Investigate Material Shortage event (12:33-12:44 on Pai-32) correlation to Material Defect root causes; cross-reference with paint supply inventory logs for batch quality issues [source: fetch_downtime_events]\n', 'type': 'text'